Enclosing interface:
RegProcedure<M extends RegProcedure.Memo.Why<M>>
public static interface RegProcedure.Memo<M extends RegProcedure.Memo<M>>
Superinterface of two memo types a RegProcedure can carry, Why and How.

A Why memo pertains to the intended use of a RegProcedure, for example as a TypeInput function or as a PlannerSupport function. The Why memo, if present, can be retrieved by the memo() method, and the type parameter of RegProcedure reflects it, as a compile-time safeguard against mixing up RegProcedures with different purposes.

Orthogonally to Why, a How memo pertains to how the RegProcedure is implemented, such as PLJavaBased if the RegProcedure is implemented in a language built atop PL/Java. The language of implementation is ideally independent of the intended use, so RegProcedure is not parameterized with a How type, and has no API method to retrieve an associated How memo. For PL/Java-based languages, PL/Java's dispatcher will pass the associated How memo to the language handler.
